HEADWORD: Soja
<hw>So"ja</hw> <pr>(s⟦omac⟧"j⟦adot⟧ ⟦or⟧ s⟦omac⟧"y⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An Asiatic leguminous herb
(<spn>Glycine max</spn>, formerly <spn>Glycine Soja</spn>) the seeds of
which (called <prod>soy beans</prod>) are used in preparing the sauce
called <prod>soy</prod>. Called also <altname>soya</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

